  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, Speer had made an attempt, a rather fragile one, but had made attempt-- an attempt to assassinate Hitler in early 1945, because he was convinced that Hitler was fighting a war where nothing would happen that would benefit Germany, except that more people would be killed and more cities devastated.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I don't believe he became actively engaged with some of the opposition forces in Germany in the military, which made the attempt on Hitler's life on July 20, 1944-- I don't think he claimed that.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I have no recall of that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But after he got-- after he was captured, he turned over all his-- the documents he had from the Central Planning Board and so on to his captors.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he became very willing to testify about his view concerning developments.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And although he wouldn't plead guilty, he did say and wrote on the indictment, 'I think there is a certain collective responsibility for what happened,' without explaining what this all was, 'during the Nazi regime.' And he wrote that on a copy of the indictment, which the prison psychologist, Dr.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Gilbert, had.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And in his interrogations, he further indicated-- and his counsel didn't oppose this too much-- that he felt responsible for the slave labor program.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But again, he denied knowledge that any of the slave laborers were sent to concentration camps to be exterminated after work.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He denied that.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
